<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Order ID</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Enter the order ID of the reorder to search for this particular reorder.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Order type</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Select the order type <strong>Reorder</strong> to restrict the search results to orders of the type <strong>reorder</strong>.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Sender</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">If you selected the order type <strong>Reorder</strong>, you can choose one of the suppliers you listed in your plentymarkets system as the sender. Select one of the suppliers if you want to search for reorders you ordered from this supplier.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Recipient</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">If you selected the order type <strong>Reorder</strong>, you can choose one of the warehouses you listed in your plentymarkets system as the receiver. Select one of the warehouses if you want to search for reorders for this warehouse.<br>
<em>Note</em>: Combine the search filters <strong>Sender</strong>, <strong>Receiver</strong> and <strong>Order type</strong> in order to specifically search for reorders that were ordered from a certain supplier and marked for a certain warehouse.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Reorder status</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Select from the drop-down list between <strong>Open</strong>, <strong>Ordered</strong> and <strong>Closed</strong>.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Item ID</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Enter an item ID to search for reorders containing an item with this ID.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Variation ID</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Enter a variation ID to search for reorders containing a variation with this ID.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Variation number</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Enter a variation number to search for reorders containing a variation with this number.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Supplier item no.</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Enter the supplier item number to search for reorders with this information.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Dealer sign</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Enter a dealer sign to search for reorders in which this dealer sign was added.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Item data</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Enter a search term or a numeric value to search for reorders that contain items with the term or number. The fields <strong>Item ID</strong>, <strong>Item number</strong> and <strong>Name</strong> are searched. The descriptive texts such as the item text and the preview text are not searched.
In addition, set the <strong>Order type</strong> filter to <strong>Reorder</strong>.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>External delivery number</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Enter the number of an external delivery note to search for reorders with this specific delivery number.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Status from</strong> and <strong>Status to</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Select a status range from the drop-down list. In addition, set the <strong>Order type</strong> filter to the option <strong>Reorder</strong> to search for reorders with this status range. If you want to search for reorders with a specific status, select the same status in both filters, <strong>Status from</strong> and <strong>Status to</strong>.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Owner</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Select an owner from the list. In addition, set the <strong>Order type</strong> filter to the option <strong>Reorder</strong> to search for reorders with this owner.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Order date type</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Choose from the drop-down list between the date types <strong>Order date</strong>, <strong>Finished date</strong>, <strong>Delivery date</strong> and <strong>Created at</strong> and select the date range with the filters <strong>Order date from</strong> and <strong>Order date to</strong>. With these settings, the reorders that were ordered, finished or created during this date range are displayed.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Order date from</strong> and <strong>Order date to</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Select a start and an end date from the calendar. In combination with the filter <strong>Order date type</strong>, reorders that were ordered, finished or created during this date range are displayed.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Tags</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Select a <a href="/en/stock-management/managing-reorders/working-with-reorders#130">tag</a> to search for reorders to which this tag was assigned. You can select several tags. This is an "or" search. This means that all reorders with at least one of the selected tags assigned are shown in the search results if you select more than one tag.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
